# BRUTE
The brute force solution to generate a matrix in spiral order is to simulate the process of filling the matrix in a spiral order. We can start by initializing the matrix with zeros and then fill the matrix in a spiral order by moving right, down, left, and up. We keep track of the current position in the matrix and the direction of movement. Whenever we reach the boundary of the matrix or encounter a non-zero element, we change the direction of movement. We continue this process until all the elements in the matrix are filled.

```java []
public int[][] generateMatrix(int n) {
        int[][] matrix = new int[n][n];
        int num = 1;
        int row = 0;
        int col = 0;
        int direction = 0;
        int[] dr = {0, 1, 0, -1};
        int[] dc = {1, 0, -1, 0};
        while (num <= n * n) {
            matrix[row][col] = num;
            num++;
            int nextRow = row + dr[direction];
            int nextCol = col + dc[direction];
            if (nextRow < 0 || nextRow >= n || nextCol < 0 || nextCol >= n || matrix[nextRow][nextCol] != 0) {
                direction = (direction + 1) % 4;
            }
            row += dr[direction];
            col += dc[direction];
        }
        return matrix;
    }
```
