# Intuition
Simple brute force

# Approach
We use left , right , top , bottom pointers to represent the configuration of the matrix.
STEPS of traversal:

1. Traverse from left to right , then update top=top+1, AS topmost row is filled.

2. Traverse from top to bottom, then update right=right-1, AS rightmost column is filled.

3. Traverse from right to left, then update bottom= bottom-1 , AS 
bottomMost row is filled.

 4. Traverse from bottom to top, then update left=left+1, 
  AS leftmost column is filled.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
  O(N*N) for traversing the matrix.

- Space complexity:
  O(N*N) for storing the matrix.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> generateMatrix(int n) {
        int num=1,left=0,right=n-1,top=0,bottom=n-1;
        vector<vector<int>>matrix(n,vector<int>(n));

        while(left<=right && top<=bottom){
            for(int i=left; i<=right; i++){
                matrix[top][i]=num++;
            }
            top++;

            for(int i=top;i<=bottom;i++){
                matrix[i][right]=num++;
            }
            right--;

            for(int i=right;i>=left;i--){
                matrix[bottom][i]=num++;
            }
            bottom--;

            for(int i=bottom;i>=top;i--){
                matrix[i][left]=num++;
            }
            left++;
        }

        return matrix;
    }
};


```

