Hi all, this code divides the whole construction into n/2 loops. In each loop, it finishes one spiral. If n is an odd number, add an extra number in the center before return.
```
class Solution {
    public int[][] generateMatrix(int n) {
        if (n==1)
            return new int [][] {{1}};
        int[][] result=new int[n][n];
        int col=0, row=0, min=0, max=n-1, i=1, loop=0;
        while(loop<n/2) {
            result[row][col]=i++;
            if (row==min && col!=max) 
                col++;
            else if(col==max && row!=max)
                row++;
            else if(row==max && col!=min) 
                col--;
            else if(col==min && row!=min+1)
                row--;
            else {
                min++;
                max--;
                col=min;
                row=min;
                loop++;
            }
        }
        if (n%2==1) 
            result[n/2][n/2]=i;
        return result;    
    }
}
```

