# Explanation 
![sol.jpg](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/b180d6a3-ee1d-43f8-99db-fe593a619c82_1689481783.411159.jpeg) 
**Correction :** We do not need to maintain int end as we can just increment start = start + len.
**Note :** substr(start, length) has first argument as starting position of susbstring and second argument as length of the substring.


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool repeatedSubstringPattern(string s) {
        int n = s.length(), i = n%2!=0 ? (n+1)/2 : n/2;
        if(n==1)    return false;
        bool flag = true;
        while(i<n){
            int start = 0, len = n-i;
            string temp = s.substr(i, len);
            flag = true;
            while(start+len < n){
                string val = s.substr(start, len);
                if(val != temp){
                    flag = false;
                    break;
                }
                start += len;
            }
            if(flag == true)    break;
            i++;
        }
        return flag;
    }
};
```

