solutions.content:
# Intuition
If such a substring exists, repeated concatenation of which gives `s`, it must:
1. Be a prefix of `s`
2. Have a length which is a divisor of length of `s` i.e. `s.size()`

So we only need to check prefixes of `s` which have lengths which are divisors of`s.size()`, also if a prefix of length `l` gets rejected, then all divisors of `l` get rejected too.
# Approach
Firstly, if length of `s` is `1`, we return false, otherwise:
We first start by finding all the divisors of `s.size()` except `s.size()` and store them in decreasing order using a set:
```
set<int,greater<int>>divs;
int n=s.size();
for(int i=2;i*i<=n;i++)
{
    if(n%i==0)
    {
        divs.insert(n/i);
        divs.insert(i);
    }
}
divs.insert(1);
```
We now check prefixes in decreasing order of their lengths:
If the current prefix keeps appearing continously in `s` till the last index, we return true, else, we remove all divisors of the length of the current prefix from the set:
```
for(auto i:divs)
{
    int j=0;
    while(j+2*i<=n&&s.substr(j,i)==s.substr(j+i,i))
    {
        j+=i;
    }
    if(j==n-i)
    {
        return true;
    }
    for(int j=2;j*j<=i;j++)
    {
        if(i%j==0)
        {
            divs.erase(j);
            divs.erase(i/j);
        }
}
```
If none of the elements of the set give the required substring, we simply return false.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n.√n)$$
`n=s.size()` can have a maximum of 2√n divisors and each of the loop checking if the prefix is a valid substring runs for a max n times (in case of divisor=1).

- Space complexity:$$O(n)$$
Self-explanatory -.- 

# Code
```
class Solution 
{
public:
    bool repeatedSubstringPattern(string s) 
    {
        if(s.size()==1)
        {
            return false;
        }
        set<int,greater<int>>divs;
        int n=s.size();
        for(int i=2;i*i<=n;i++)
        {
            if(n%i==0)
            {
                divs.insert(n/i);
                divs.insert(i);
            }
        }
        divs.insert(1);
        n=s.size();
        for(auto i:divs)
        {
            int j=0;
            while(j+2*i<=n&&s.substr(j,i)==s.substr(j+i,i))
            {
                j+=i;
            }
            if(j==n-i)
            {
                return true;
            }
            for(int j=2;j*j<=i;j++)
            {
                if(i%j==0)
                {
                    divs.erase(j);
                    divs.erase(i/j);
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};
```

