subs = prefix of string s;
n = s.length(), m = subs.length()
One necessary condition of subs to build s is that m must divide n.
Finding all the factors is O(rootn) time and checking if its a pattern is O(n) time.
Overall time complexity is O(nrootn)  < O(n2)
If n^2 solutions are accepted then nrootn must surely be accepted.
But it's giving me TLE!!



