The idea here is very intuitive...
We create an auxiliary matrix of size nXm, where m is the number of rows in the original matrix and n is the number of columns in the original matrix...
Now, we simply traverse the original matrix and fill up the auxiliary matrix in transpose order...
Transpose order implies --> matrix[i][j] = auxiliary[j][i] 

**Pls upvote this thread if you found it helpful**

