### **Note:** 
In **C#** there are two types or arrays: **Jagged Arrays - Multidimensional Arrays**. The main difference between them that we have to **intialize** every **row** (array) in the **jagged** to specify the length of it (**cols**). There are more differences but i mentioned the one that suites this problem.

### **For more info please read the docuentation.**
**Multidimensional Arrays:**
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/csharp/programming-guide/arrays/multidimensional-arrays
**Jagged Arrays:**
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/csharp/programming-guide/arrays/jagged-arrays
### **Solution:**



```
public class Solution {
    public int[][] Transpose(int[][] matrix) {
        int row = matrix.Length, col = matrix[0].Length;  // We get the rows and cols of the matrix.
        int[][] transpose = new int[col][];  // Declaring a Jagged array
        for(int i = 0; i < col; i++){
            transpose[i] = new int[row]; // Intialize every row in the jagged array
            for(int j = 0; j < row; j++)
                transpose[i][j] = matrix[j][i];
        }
        return transpose;
    }
}
```
