# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
*Matrix transposition is like rotating a grid of numbers by 90 degrees. ```Rows become columns, and columns become rows.```*
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Step 1: Determine Dimensions
```
// Determine the dimensions of the original matrix
int rows = originalMatrix.length;
int cols = originalMatrix[0].length;
```
Step 2: Create a New Matrix

```
// Create a new matrix with swapped dimensions
int[][] transposedMatrix = new int[cols][rows];
```
Step 3: Iterate Through the Original Matrix

Step 4: Swap Elements

```
// Swap elements to transpose the matrix
transposedMatrix[j][i] = originalMatrix[i][j];
```
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

