# Intuition
We will use hashmap or array and also use the concept of prefix sum to solve this problem.
![WhatsApp Image 2023-01-19 at 7.06.08 AM.jpeg](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/7ec413ac-360c-4a90-98a2-64dccd7cb91f_1674092298.9756303.jpeg)

<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
1. Initialize an empty vector called "output" of size "k" to keep track of the count of subarrays that have the same remainder when divided by "k".
2. Initialize a variable "prefixMod" to store the current prefix sum modulo "k" and a variable "res" to store the total count of subarrays that have a remainder of 0 when divided by "k".
3. Set the first element of "output" to 1, this is because the first prefix sum would have a remainder of 0.
4. Iterate through each element "nums[i]" in the input vector "nums".
5. Calculate the current prefix sum modulo "k" by adding the current element "nums[i]" to the previous prefix sum modulo "k" and taking the remainder when divided by "k".
6. Add the count of subarrays that have the same remainder to "res" by getting the value of the corresponding index in the "output" vector.
7. Increase the count of subarrays that have the same remainder by 1 by incrementing the value of the corresponding index in the "output" vector.
8. Return the total count of subarrays that have a remainder of 0 when divided by "k" stored in "res".
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Code
```C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    int subarraysDivByK(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        vector<int> output(k, 0);
        // prefixModSum is used to store sum of all prefix mods
        int prefixModSum = 0;
        int res = 0;
        output[0] = 1;
        for(int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++){
            // (nums[i] % k + k) is used to avoid nagative remsinder
            prefixModSum = (prefixModSum + nums[i] % k + k) % k;
            //If in test case, only positive number given like [5,0,5,3] then
            //prefixModSum = prefixModSum + nums[i] % k;
            // Add the count of subarrays that have the same remainder
            res = res + output[prefixModSum];
            output[prefixModSum]++;
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
