solutions.content:
Property Of prefix Sum array

    prefix[i] stores the sum till ith index

    So if we want to find the sum of all elements from i to j, it can be found by : sum_i_to_j = prefix[j] - prefix[i-1]
    also we require that sum_i_to_j should be divisible by K

    which means

    sum_i_to_j % k = 0

    (prefix[j] - prefix[i-1]) % k = 0 --- (1)

    any number can be written as dividend = divisor * quotient  + remainder

    so lets say prefix[j] = Mk + x ,    and prefix[i-1] = Nk + y

    substituting in the above equation

    ((Mk + x) - (Nk + y)) % k = 0

    ((M-N)k + (x - y)) % k = 0

    ((M-N)k%k + (x-y)%k) % k = 0

    ((x%k - y%k)%k)%k = (x - y) % k = 0  --- (2)

    now from equation 2, we have (x - y) % k = 0, means (x - y should be a multiple of k), so (x - y) = Qk

    x = Qk + y

    x%k = y%k

    so we infer from the above relation that, if at any point we find the remainder, and there exist a point till where we get the same remainder, the subarray enclosed in between those (excluding the left point)
    will be divisible by K

    Now what to do if the remainder comes out to be negative

    for example when in C++, when we do -1 % 2 , we get the result as -1 , whereas in reality the remainder is 1
    so the remedy here is to just add the divisor whenever the remainder is -ve

    so if remainder < 0, remainder += k;

