# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The brute-force solution is that we iterate over each subarray and check if the subarray sum is divisible by k but this solution will give us TLE given the constraints.
#### So, the main question is whelther you can access all subarrays in a better way (less than O(n^2))?

The answer to the above question is **PREFIX SUM ARRAY**.
Using Prefix sum array we can access all the subarrays in O(n).
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Construct a prefix sum array
2. Find modulo of every element of prefix sum array with 'k'
3. Find the required pairs using frequency stored in map
4. Rest explaination in comments.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(nLogn)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
**Optimized Solution**: Prefix Array can be replaced by an variable to store the current_sum and map can be replaced by an array of size 'k'.
This will reduce the time complexity to O(n). 
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int subarraysDivByK(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> prefix_nums(n,0);
        prefix_nums[0] = nums[0]%k;
        if(prefix_nums[0] < 0){
            prefix_nums[0] += k;
        }
        for(int i=1; i<n; i++){
            prefix_nums[i] = prefix_nums[i-1] + nums[i];
            prefix_nums[i] %= k;
            if(prefix_nums[i] < 0){
                prefix_nums[i] += k;
            }
        }

        // here we are done creating a prefixArray
        // i.e. when nums = [4,5,0,-2,-3,1] && k = 5
        // the prefix array would be 
        // prefix_nums = [4,9,9,7,4,5]
        // but we aren't done yet, we also take its modulo with k
        // so, final prefix_nums = [4,4,4,2,4,0]
        // at this point its quiet intuitive why the answer is 7 in this case
        // but still here are the index-pairs
        // (0,1), (0,2), (0,4)
        // (1,2), (1,4)
        // (2,4)
        // (5,5) --> this can be treated as a special case

        map<int,int> m;
        int ans{};
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            ans += m[prefix_nums[i]];
            m[prefix_nums[i]]++;
            if(prefix_nums[i] == 0)ans++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

