```
The approch here is , we store remainders and its freq in a Hashmap. if we encounter a remainder frequency twice
it means we have a subarray sum starting from index 0 to that particular index where frequency was 2 minus sum
from index 0 to index where remainder frequency was 1 , this subarray sum is divisible by p.

class Solution {
    public int subarraysDivByK(int[] arr, int k) {
         int result = 0;

        Map<Integer , Integer>map = new HashMap<>();
        map.put(0 , 1);

        int sum = 0;
        int rem = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++){
            sum += arr[i];
            rem = sum % k;

            if(rem < 0)
                rem += k;

            if(map.containsKey(rem)){
                result += map.get(rem);
                map.put(rem , map.get(rem)+1);
            }
            else{
                map.put(rem , 1);
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}

