EDGE CASE HANDLING - if there are negative remainders , DONT MAP THEM DIRECTLY, you have to map them to a number corresponding to its positive side, which is calculated by addaing (k) tot he negative number and then doing similar operations on it as that of a positive remainder.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N) 

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int subarraysDivByK(vector<int>& nums, int k) 
    {
        int n = nums.size();//size of the nums array
        int sum = 0;
        int rem = 0;
        int ans = 0;//storing the final count
        unordered_map<int,int> map;
        map[rem] = 1;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            sum += nums[i];//pehle sum me add kiya us index ko
            rem = sum % k;//fir uska modulo liya jo bhi k given hai.remainder nikala
