## Approach:

* For each index i, count all prev prefix sums in the array which has modulo same as of curr prefix sum(at idx i) and add it to result.
`Use HashTable to store the counts of prefix sum modulo.`
* Also, for a `-ve number` num, `num%k<0`, we have to change it to `+ve mod` because modulo of a number can lie in the range of `0 to k-1` only.

Let, num = -2, k=3 then `res=(-2)%3=-2`, for changing it to +ve mod add k to res.
Changing to +ve mod, `-2+3 = 1`, So, `res=(-2)%3=1`.

![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/059599f6-1784-4eaa-861d-0cb9cbf57d72_1674096562.5566626.png)


## Complexity:
- Time complexity: O(n)
- Space complexity: O(k)

## Code
``` java []
class Solution {
    public int subarraysDivByK(int[] nums, int k) {
        int[] freq = new int[k]; //mod value can only be in range of 0 to k-1
        freq[0]=1;
        int prefixSum=0, subArrays=0;
        for(int x:nums)
        {
            prefixSum+=x;
            int mod = prefixSum%k;
            //changing -ve mod to +ve mod because mod can only in the range of 0 to k-1
            if(mod<0){ 
                mod+=k;
            }
            //adding the prev count of mod to subarrays and incrementing freq[mod] as well
            subArrays+=freq[mod]++; 
        }
        return subArrays;
    }
}
```
