solutions.content:
This question requires basic concept we used in maths for solving problems in class 10!!!
We have to find a subarray whose sum is divisible by a given number. 
## Brute Force
The brute force will be to generate all subarray and add their elements then find the count.
Time complexity will be O(N^3) to generate subarray and then O(N) to add the subarray elements.
You can **optimise the time complexity of generating subarrays** to O(N^2)

## Optimised Approach
Say there is two sum S1, S2. These numbers on dividing with k gives remainder x. Thus, these numbers can be written as
S1= kn+x
S2= km+x
So if we can see S2-S1 = (km+x) - (kn+x) = k(m-n) which is divisible by k. Hence, this is what we have to find!!!
If we have remainder negative just add k to it as it makes positive and pair to k for divisibility.

So basic idea is get current sum, find remainder(donot forget to check negative remainder case), then store their frequency in map. If you get same remainder, add the frequency to your array.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int subarraysDivByK(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        unordered_map<int,int> remCount;
        int res=0,rem=0,sum=0;
        remCount[rem] = 1;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++) {
            sum += nums[i];
            rem = sum%k;
            rem = (rem < 0) ? (rem+k):rem;
            if(remCount.find(rem) != remCount.end()) {
                res += remCount[rem];
            }
            ++remCount[rem];
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

